<h3>The Practical Framework</h3>
<p>Most advice says to choose either SEO or conversions. That is wrong. Here is how to do both.</p>
<p><strong>Above the fold:</strong> Conversion-first. Clear headline. Value proposition. Primary CTA. Hero image or video. This serves both humans and Google.</p>
<p><strong>Below the fold:</strong> SEO-first. Detailed content covering the topic. Secondary keywords. FAQ sections. Internal links. Social proof. This gives Google the depth it needs while building trust for visitors who scroll.</p>
<p><strong>Navigation:</strong> Keep it. But make it sticky and compact. Removing navigation hurts SEO (fewer crawl paths) even though it boosts conversion in paid contexts. On SEO landing pages, navigation helps Google discover related pages and distributes link equity.</p>
<p><strong>CTAs:</strong> Place them at natural break points. Use soft CTAs in content ("see how it works," "start free trial") and one strong CTA above fold. Google understands commercial intent pages. CTAs do not hurt rankings.</p>
